Day 28:
Step 0: Sign in to your organization (https://dev.azure.com/{Your_Organization}).

________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________


1. Set up an organization over Azure DevOps services and create a Private project (Note: Use Agile Process)
Step 1: Sign in to your Azure DevOps Organisation.
Step 2: Select new organisation.
Step 3: Enter the name for your organization, select its hosting geography, and then select Continue.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

---> Creating an Private project using Agile Process:
Step 1: Select New project.
Step 2: Enter the following details:
      a. Project name
      b. Description
      c. Agile Process
      d. Public
Step 3: Select Create.

_______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

2. Create multiple work items and create hierarchy among these work items:
Step 1: Go to Boards and in Boards select Backlogs.
Step 2: Click on to create an new work item.

_____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

3. Create a sprint over Azure Boards:
Step 1: Select SPRINTS in Boards,
Step 2: Click on Iterations to ADD or View you sprints.

_____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
